1
00:01:57,099 --> 00:01:59,090
Katie!

2
00:01:59,769 --> 00:02:01,259
Cora!

3
00:02:01,570 --> 00:02:03,037
You love your sister?

4
00:02:03,372 --> 00:02:05,806
You make any noise,
you know what happens.

5
00:02:52,354 --> 00:02:53,787
Good morning, Estelle.

6
00:02:54,123 --> 00:02:57,684
- How am I looking, Paul?
- That's better. That's better.

7
00:03:14,009 --> 00:03:15,408
Morning, Mr. Edgecomb.

8
00:03:15,878 --> 00:03:17,038
Some Danish?

9
00:03:17,313 --> 00:03:20,407
No, just two pieces of
dry toast, Hector. Thanks.

10
00:03:20,683 --> 00:03:22,014
Leftover's fine.

11
00:03:22,318 --> 00:03:24,343
Dry and cold, same as always.

12
00:03:24,720 --> 00:03:25,618
Cold is better.

13
00:03:27,423 --> 00:03:29,152
Especially on those long walks.

14
00:03:30,759 --> 00:03:31,726
Am I right?

15
00:03:33,429 --> 00:03:36,796
Don't let Nurse Godzilla catch you.
She'll raise holy hell.

16
00:03:37,066 --> 00:03:39,091
We're not supposed to
let you wander off.

17
00:03:42,104 --> 00:03:46,302
Where do you go every day?
What do you do up in those hills?

18
00:03:46,876 --> 00:03:48,400
Just walk.

19
00:03:49,111 --> 00:03:50,510
I like to walk.

20
00:03:53,182 --> 00:03:55,047
Try not to fall down, bust a hip.

21
00:03:55,784 --> 00:03:58,082
I don't wanna be in no
damn search party.

22
00:05:08,023 --> 00:05:12,289
You want this man in your life?
Explain the moral basis of that.

23
00:05:12,561 --> 00:05:13,493
I've made mistakes.

24
00:05:13,829 --> 00:05:16,696
Tony doesn't admit that
he's not a good father.

25
00:05:16,966 --> 00:05:19,935
You can't ask nothing.
I have six kids myself.

26
00:05:21,904 --> 00:05:23,735
Why do we always watch this stuff?

27
00:05:24,607 --> 00:05:25,972
It's interesting.

28
00:05:27,042 --> 00:05:31,342
Interesting?
Bunch of inbred trailer trash?

29
00:05:31,614 --> 00:05:34,082
All they ever talk about is fucking.

30
00:05:56,138 --> 00:05:58,003
Are you all right?

31
00:05:59,308 --> 00:06:01,708
You look tired. You're not yourself.

32
00:06:02,011 --> 00:06:04,605
No, I'm fine. I promise.

33
00:06:05,080 --> 00:06:08,709
You're wearing yourself out
with those walks every day, I think.

34
00:06:08,984 --> 00:06:10,849
Not that you asked me.

35
00:06:11,287 --> 00:06:13,983
I just didn't sleep well, is all.

36
00:06:15,090 --> 00:06:18,321
I had a few bad dreams. It happens.

37
00:06:18,594 --> 00:06:20,186
I'll be fine.

38
00:06:28,804 --> 00:06:31,295
If Madge doesn't care,
I certainly don't.

39
00:06:31,607 --> 00:06:32,631
Neither do I.

40
00:06:33,542 --> 00:06:35,476
Now, this here is worth a look.

41
00:06:37,413 --> 00:06:39,244
I'm in heaven

42
00:06:40,516 --> 00:06:45,419
And my heart beats so
That I can hardly speak

43
00:06:46,922 --> 00:06:48,787
And I seem to find

44
00:06:49,058 --> 00:06:52,687
The happiness I seek

45
00:06:53,262 --> 00:06:56,163
When we're out together

46
00:06:56,432 --> 00:06:59,333
Dancing cheek to cheek

47
00:07:00,469 --> 00:07:02,232
Heaven

48
00:07:02,871 --> 00:07:05,271
I'm in heaven

49
00:07:06,241 --> 00:07:08,766
And the cares that hung around me

50
00:07:09,078 --> 00:07:11,808
Through the week

51
00:07:12,514 --> 00:07:13,776
Seem to vanish

52
00:07:14,049 --> 00:07:17,041
Like a gambler's lucky streak

53
00:07:21,023 --> 00:07:22,422
Paul, what is it?

54
00:07:24,860 --> 00:07:26,259
My God.

55
00:07:31,567 --> 00:07:33,797
I've got to get out of here.

56
00:07:55,858 --> 00:07:59,225
I guess sometimes the past
just catches up with you...

57
00:07:59,528 --> 00:08:02,520
...whether you want it to or not.
It's silly.

58
00:08:03,031 --> 00:08:06,296
Was it the film? It was, wasn't it?

59
00:08:07,603 --> 00:08:11,972
I haven't spoken of these things
for a long time, Ellie.

60
00:08:12,241 --> 00:08:13,572
Over 60 years.

61
00:08:13,842 --> 00:08:16,572
Paul, I'm your friend.

62
00:08:21,216 --> 00:08:24,845
I ever tell you that I was
a prison guard during the Depression?

63
00:08:25,187 --> 00:08:26,916
You've mentioned it.

64
00:08:27,890 --> 00:08:30,290
Did I mention I was
in charge of death row?

65
00:08:30,626 --> 00:08:32,753
That I supervised all the executions?

66
00:08:37,399 --> 00:08:41,836
Usually, death row is called
"The Last Mile."

67
00:08:42,271 --> 00:08:44,671
We called ours "The Green Mile."

68
00:08:45,441 --> 00:08:48,376
The floor was the color
of faded limes.

69
00:08:49,344 --> 00:08:51,869
We had the electric chair.

70
00:08:52,481 --> 00:08:54,142
"Old Sparky," we called it.

71
00:08:56,652 --> 00:08:59,382
I've lived a lot of years, Ellie...

72
00:09:00,289 --> 00:09:04,020
...but 1935, that takes the prize.

73
00:09:05,427 --> 00:09:07,122
That year, I had...

74
00:09:07,429 --> 00:09:10,592
...the worst urinary infection
of my life.

75
00:09:12,367 --> 00:09:13,732
It was...

76
00:09:14,837 --> 00:09:17,032
It was also the year of...

77
00:09:17,606 --> 00:09:19,699
...John Coffey...

78
00:09:20,943 --> 00:09:23,309
...and the two dead girls.

79
00:10:38,487 --> 00:10:39,886
Put me through to E Block.

80
00:10:53,969 --> 00:10:55,334
E Block.

81
00:10:57,639 --> 00:10:58,799
Right.

82
00:11:19,928 --> 00:11:22,226
Paul? Prisoner.

83
00:11:22,497 --> 00:11:23,987
Christ, give me a minute.

84
00:11:29,671 --> 00:11:30,831
You all right?

85
00:11:33,575 --> 00:11:37,443
For a man pissing razorblades, yeah.

86
00:11:51,994 --> 00:11:54,326
You should've took the day off
to see the doctor.

87
00:11:54,596 --> 00:11:57,258
With the new arrival?
You know better.

88
00:11:57,933 --> 00:11:59,332
Besides...

89
00:11:59,935 --> 00:12:03,336
...it's not as bad as it was.
I think it's clearing up.

90
00:12:06,608 --> 00:12:08,303
- Let's look alive, Dean.
- Yes, sir.

91
00:12:15,784 --> 00:12:16,842
Damn.

92
00:12:18,320 --> 00:12:20,185
They're riding on the axle.

93
00:12:29,898 --> 00:12:31,263
What'd they do?

94
00:12:32,134 --> 00:12:33,260
They bust the springs?

95
00:12:42,077 --> 00:12:43,544
Dead man!

96
00:12:44,413 --> 00:12:46,005
Dead man walking!

97
00:12:47,482 --> 00:12:49,746
We got a dead man walking here!

98
00:12:50,686 --> 00:12:53,052
Jesus please us,
what is he yelling about?

99
00:12:58,326 --> 00:13:01,193
You might reconsider getting
in the cell with this guy.

100
00:13:01,463 --> 00:13:02,828
He's enormous.

101
00:13:03,098 --> 00:13:04,998
Can't be bigger than you.

102
00:13:15,544 --> 00:13:16,806
Dead man!

103
00:13:17,946 --> 00:13:19,140
Dead man walking!

104
00:13:19,414 --> 00:13:20,813
Dead man!

105
00:13:21,416 --> 00:13:22,508
Dead man walking!

106
00:13:23,719 --> 00:13:25,687
Dead man walking here!

107
00:13:27,055 --> 00:13:28,249
Dead man!

108
00:13:32,027 --> 00:13:33,756
We got a dead man walking here!

109
00:13:35,430 --> 00:13:36,624
Dead man walking!

110
00:13:38,767 --> 00:13:41,463
- We got a dead man walking here!
- Percy.

111
00:13:42,971 --> 00:13:44,165
That's enough.

112
00:14:07,429 --> 00:14:09,795
Am I gonna have any trouble
with you, big boy?

113
00:14:14,936 --> 00:14:15,925
Can you talk?

114
00:14:21,943 --> 00:14:25,504
Yes, sir, boss. I can talk.

115
00:14:34,122 --> 00:14:34,986
Move your ass.

116
00:14:35,657 --> 00:14:36,589
Let's go.

117
00:14:37,259 --> 00:14:38,556
Come on.

118
00:14:43,932 --> 00:14:44,796
Percy...

119
00:14:46,802 --> 00:14:48,963
...they're moving house
in the infirmary.

120
00:14:49,604 --> 00:14:52,471
Why don't you go see
if they could use some help?

121
00:14:53,275 --> 00:14:54,833
They got all the men they need.

122
00:14:55,610 --> 00:14:57,134
Why don't you just make sure?

123
00:15:00,115 --> 00:15:03,676
I don't care where you go, as long as
it's not here at this moment.

124
00:15:08,056 --> 00:15:09,284
All right.

125
00:15:22,370 --> 00:15:24,531
God, you bust my finger.

126
00:15:24,806 --> 00:15:27,138
I wiped that grin
off your face, didn't I?

127
00:15:27,409 --> 00:15:29,673
Goddamn it, Percy,
get the hell off my block!

128
00:15:42,691 --> 00:15:43,680
Fuck you, Percy.

129
00:15:44,059 --> 00:15:47,187
We'll get that looked at, Del.
In the meantime, stay quiet.

130
00:15:53,935 --> 00:15:56,495
I let Harry take those chains off you...

131
00:15:57,172 --> 00:15:58,366
...you gonna be nice?

132
00:16:15,590 --> 00:16:17,057
Your name is John Coffey.

133
00:16:17,525 --> 00:16:18,992
Yes, sir, boss.

134
00:16:19,361 --> 00:16:22,728
Like the drink,
only not spelt the same.

135
00:16:23,198 --> 00:16:24,563
You can spell, can you?

136
00:16:25,467 --> 00:16:28,163
Just my name, boss.

137
00:16:28,970 --> 00:16:31,268
J... O...

138
00:16:31,773 --> 00:16:33,638
My name is Paul Edgecomb.

139
00:16:34,643 --> 00:16:37,339
If I'm not here, you can
ask for Mr. Terwilliger...

140
00:16:37,612 --> 00:16:40,604
...Mr. Howell or Mr. Stanton.
These gentlemen right there.

141
00:16:43,218 --> 00:16:44,242
Questions?

142
00:16:45,153 --> 00:16:47,451
Do you leave the light on
after bedtime?

143
00:16:50,225 --> 00:16:53,626
Because I get a little scared
in the dark sometime...

144
00:16:54,396 --> 00:16:56,887
...if it's a strange place.

145
00:17:01,836 --> 00:17:05,772
It stays pretty bright around here
all night long.

146
00:17:06,074 --> 00:17:08,565
We keep a few lights burning
in the corridor.

147
00:17:09,778 --> 00:17:11,678
The corridor?

148
00:17:13,348 --> 00:17:14,713
Right out there.

149
00:17:42,944 --> 00:17:44,411
You can sit.

150
00:18:06,801 --> 00:18:09,099
I couldn't help it, boss.

151
00:18:09,471 --> 00:18:12,770
I tried to take it back,
but it was too late.

152
00:18:19,014 --> 00:18:22,973
Take Delacroix to the infirmary,
see if those fingers are broken.

153
00:18:23,284 --> 00:18:25,752
Of course they are.
I heard the bones crack.

154
00:18:26,087 --> 00:18:28,783
You hear what he was yelling
when we brought the dummy in?

155
00:18:29,090 --> 00:18:30,955
How could I miss it?
The whole prison heard.

156
00:18:31,860 --> 00:18:33,054
Goddamn Percy.

157
00:18:33,862 --> 00:18:36,729
You'll have to answer
for sending him off the Mile.

158
00:18:37,465 --> 00:18:39,865
I'll chew that food when I have to.

159
00:18:40,268 --> 00:18:44,568
Right now I wanna hear about this
new inmate. Aside from how big he is.

160
00:18:45,240 --> 00:18:47,470
Monstrous big. Damn.

161
00:18:47,742 --> 00:18:49,642
He seems meek enough.

162
00:18:49,944 --> 00:18:51,639
Is he retarded, you figure?

163
00:18:52,380 --> 00:18:54,746
Looks like they sent us
an imbecile to execute.

164
00:18:55,016 --> 00:18:58,247
Imbecile or not,
he deserves to fry for what he done.

165
00:19:01,890 --> 00:19:03,824
Make your blood curdle.

166
00:19:27,749 --> 00:19:31,776
- What?! For God's sake, what?
- The girls! The girls are gone!

167
00:19:32,654 --> 00:19:35,487
Papa! Papa, look! There's blood.

168
00:19:39,928 --> 00:19:41,623
Oh, my God.

169
00:19:46,935 --> 00:19:50,871
Goddamn it, woman! Get on that phone.
You tell them we headed west.

170
00:19:51,172 --> 00:19:54,164
You mind what I'm saying!
We headed west!

171
00:19:54,476 --> 00:19:56,842
Central! Are you on the line?

172
00:19:57,112 --> 00:20:01,208
Oh, God, please.
Somebody took my little girls.

173
00:20:12,760 --> 00:20:14,318
IKatie!

174
00:20:15,396 --> 00:20:16,863
Cora!

175
00:20:47,996 --> 00:20:49,429
Jesus.

176
00:20:50,498 --> 00:20:51,897
Jesus.

177
00:21:02,844 --> 00:21:04,175
I'll kill you!

178
00:21:08,016 --> 00:21:09,574
I'll kill you!

179
00:21:38,513 --> 00:21:40,037
I couldn't help it.

180
00:21:41,182 --> 00:21:44,640
I tried to take it back,
but it was too late.

181
00:21:48,423 --> 00:21:51,449
Boy, you under arrest for murder.

182
00:21:53,628 --> 00:21:55,061
I interrupt?

183
00:21:56,731 --> 00:21:59,291
Well, I'm just about done.

184
00:22:11,179 --> 00:22:12,578
How's your pretty gal?

185
00:22:14,582 --> 00:22:16,777
Melinda's not so well, Paul.

186
00:22:17,585 --> 00:22:18,609
Not so well at all.

187
00:22:20,655 --> 00:22:21,952
More headaches?

188
00:22:22,624 --> 00:22:25,115
Got laid up with another one yesterday.

189
00:22:25,893 --> 00:22:27,258
Worst one yet.

190
00:22:28,029 --> 00:22:31,897
I'll be taking her over to Vicksburg
next day or so for some tests.

191
00:22:32,967 --> 00:22:35,697
Head x-rays and who knows what else.

192
00:22:35,970 --> 00:22:38,666
She is scared to death.

193
00:22:40,808 --> 00:22:42,708
Truth to tell, so am I.

194
00:22:44,045 --> 00:22:46,878
If it's something they can see
on the x-ray...

195
00:22:47,548 --> 00:22:49,277
...maybe they can fix it.

196
00:22:50,385 --> 00:22:51,477
Maybe.

197
00:22:56,157 --> 00:22:57,681
This just came in.

198
00:22:58,026 --> 00:23:00,324
DOE on Bitterbuck.

199
00:23:03,398 --> 00:23:05,798
You didn't come down here
to hand me a DOE.

200
00:23:06,968 --> 00:23:10,904
I had an angry call from the
state capitol about 20 minutes ago.

201
00:23:11,539 --> 00:23:13,837
Is it true you ordered Percy Wetmore
off the block?

202
00:23:14,108 --> 00:23:15,336
It is.

203
00:23:16,311 --> 00:23:19,747
Now, I'm sure you had reason, Paul...

204
00:23:20,048 --> 00:23:23,745
...but like it or not, the wife
of the governor has only one nephew...

205
00:23:24,052 --> 00:23:25,815
...and his name is Percy Wetmore.

206
00:23:26,187 --> 00:23:27,984
Little Percy calls his aunt...

207
00:23:28,289 --> 00:23:31,656
...and squeals like a schoolroom sissy.

208
00:23:33,328 --> 00:23:37,389
He mention he assaulted a prisoner
this morning out of sheer petulance?

209
00:23:37,699 --> 00:23:40,361
Broke three fingers
on Eduard Delacroix's left hand.

210
00:23:40,668 --> 00:23:43,159
I didn't hear that.
I'm sure she didn't either.

211
00:23:43,471 --> 00:23:45,302
He is mean, careless and stupid...

212
00:23:45,573 --> 00:23:48,269
...and that's a bad combination
in a place like this.

213
00:23:48,609 --> 00:23:51,043
Sooner or later, he'll get
somebody hurt or worse.

214
00:23:51,346 --> 00:23:52,608
Stick with it, Paul.

215
00:23:53,047 --> 00:23:54,537
It may not be much longer.

216
00:23:54,849 --> 00:23:59,252
I have it on good authority that Percy
has an application in at Briar Ridge.

217
00:23:59,520 --> 00:24:02,011
Briar Ridge? The mental hospital.

218
00:24:02,390 --> 00:24:03,618
Administration job.

219
00:24:04,058 --> 00:24:05,320
Better pay.

220
00:24:07,028 --> 00:24:08,996
Then why is he still here?

221
00:24:11,032 --> 00:24:13,227
He can get that application
pushed through.

222
00:24:15,570 --> 00:24:18,733
With his connections, he could have
any state job he wants.

223
00:24:19,607 --> 00:24:21,165
You know what I think?

224
00:24:23,378 --> 00:24:26,779
I think he just wants to
see one cook up close.

225
00:24:29,751 --> 00:24:33,687
Well, he'll get his chance, then.
Won't he?

226
00:24:34,722 --> 00:24:38,715
Maybe then he'll be satisfied
and move on. In the meantime...

227
00:24:39,394 --> 00:24:40,759
...you'll keep the peace?

228
00:24:41,028 --> 00:24:42,256
Of course.

229
00:24:43,731 --> 00:24:44,857
Of course.

230
00:24:46,734 --> 00:24:47,894
Thank you, Paul.

231
00:24:51,939 --> 00:24:52,906
Hal...

232
00:24:54,475 --> 00:24:56,466
...you give Melinda my love, okay?

233
00:24:57,078 --> 00:25:01,242
I'm sure that x-ray will turn out
to be nothing at all.

234
00:25:02,650 --> 00:25:03,776
You bet.

235
00:25:34,949 --> 00:25:36,280
The music too loud?

236
00:25:38,386 --> 00:25:41,878
There's just this empty spot
in the bed where my husband sleeps.

237
00:25:44,625 --> 00:25:48,117
He said to tell you he's having
a little trouble with that tonight.

238
00:25:51,699 --> 00:25:53,758
Worried about Melinda and Hal?

239
00:25:54,569 --> 00:25:56,434
Is that what's got you up?

240
00:25:57,205 --> 00:25:59,139
Yeah, that...

241
00:26:00,575 --> 00:26:01,974
...and things.

242
00:26:03,077 --> 00:26:04,476
Things.

243
00:26:08,950 --> 00:26:12,113
We got a new inmate today.

244
00:26:12,854 --> 00:26:14,754
Simple-minded fella.

245
00:26:16,257 --> 00:26:18,225
Do I wanna know what he did?

246
00:26:19,494 --> 00:26:20,392
No.

247
00:26:21,929 --> 00:26:24,022
Things that happen in this world.

248
00:26:25,700 --> 00:26:27,793
It's a wonder God allows it.

249
00:26:32,273 --> 00:26:34,104
Why don't you come to bed?

250
00:26:35,009 --> 00:26:38,001
I think I have something
that'll help you sleep.

251
00:26:39,514 --> 00:26:41,505
You can have all you want.

252
00:26:42,717 --> 00:26:45,185
I still got something wrong
with my waterworks.

253
00:26:45,486 --> 00:26:47,386
I don't wanna pass it on to you.

254
00:26:47,788 --> 00:26:49,722
Have you seen Doc Bishop yet?

255
00:26:50,024 --> 00:26:50,991
No.

256
00:26:53,294 --> 00:26:55,421
He'll want me to take sulfa tablets...

257
00:26:55,730 --> 00:26:58,130
...and I'll spend the week
puking in my office.

258
00:26:58,399 --> 00:27:02,358
It will run its course by itself.
Thank you very much for your concern.

259
00:27:05,373 --> 00:27:06,772
Poor old guy.

260
00:27:34,302 --> 00:27:38,932
The legislature loosened up the purse
strings enough to hire on a new guard.

261
00:27:47,748 --> 00:27:48,840
Look again.

262
00:27:49,317 --> 00:27:50,579
He's right...

263
00:27:50,985 --> 00:27:51,952
