00:52:08,708 --> 00:52:10,573
Finally hit the big time.

521
00:52:12,045 --> 00:52:15,242
IKilled three people in a holdup.

522
00:52:15,548 --> 00:52:17,573
One of them a pregnant woman.

523
00:52:20,219 --> 00:52:22,119
Bad news all around.

524
00:52:36,602 --> 00:52:37,762
It's a tumor, Paul.

525
00:52:39,539 --> 00:52:41,166
A brain tumor.

526
00:52:43,009 --> 00:52:44,067
They got...

527
00:52:45,011 --> 00:52:47,002
...x- ray pictures of it.

528
00:52:48,514 --> 00:52:50,948
It's the size of a lemon, they said.

529
00:52:53,753 --> 00:52:54,879
And...

530
00:52:56,222 --> 00:52:57,621
...way down...

531
00:52:59,559 --> 00:53:01,652
...deep inside,
where they can't operate.

532
00:53:03,796 --> 00:53:05,354
I haven't told her.

533
00:53:07,233 --> 00:53:09,133
I can't think how.

534
00:53:12,972 --> 00:53:14,997
For the life of me, Paul...

535
00:53:16,609 --> 00:53:19,510
...I can't think how to
tell my wife...

536
00:53:23,082 --> 00:53:24,982
...she's going to die.

537
00:54:49,702 --> 00:54:51,693
Oh, oh, God.

538
00:54:52,471 --> 00:54:53,938
Oh, God.

539
00:54:57,910 --> 00:54:59,241
I'm going.

540
00:54:59,512 --> 00:55:00,376
What?

541
00:55:00,646 --> 00:55:03,410
To see Dr. Bishop. I'm going.

542
00:55:03,849 --> 00:55:05,248
Today.

543
00:55:05,818 --> 00:55:08,412
Soon as we get that new inmate
squared away.

544
00:55:08,921 --> 00:55:09,979
That bad?

545
00:55:10,823 --> 00:55:12,188
Oh, yeah.

546
00:55:34,347 --> 00:55:36,440
The boy's doped to the gills.

547
00:55:39,518 --> 00:55:40,610
Hand me them clothes.

548
00:55:43,789 --> 00:55:45,620
William Wharton?

549
00:55:47,460 --> 00:55:49,257
You put on these clothes now.

550
00:55:57,436 --> 00:55:58,460
We'll have to do this.

551
00:56:00,773 --> 00:56:02,297
Hellraiser, huh?

552
00:56:02,608 --> 00:56:05,168
Look more like a limp noodle to me.

553
00:56:09,048 --> 00:56:12,745
You've been declared competent, son.
You know what that means?

554
00:56:13,586 --> 00:56:15,144
You're gonna ride the lightning.

555
00:56:18,391 --> 00:56:19,881
Shut up, give us a hand.

556
00:56:20,893 --> 00:56:22,485
Hellraiser.

557
00:56:53,559 --> 00:56:54,958
You don't look so good.

558
00:56:57,029 --> 00:56:58,929
Look like you're running you a fever.

559
00:57:04,770 --> 00:57:06,260
Boss Edgecomb?

560
00:57:07,873 --> 00:57:09,738
I needs to see you down here.

561
00:57:12,378 --> 00:57:14,573
I got things to tend to, John Coffey.

562
00:57:17,350 --> 00:57:20,615
You just stay still in your cell.

563
00:57:32,298 --> 00:57:33,424
E Block.

564
00:58:09,769 --> 00:58:11,168
Come on, let's go.

565
00:58:12,505 --> 00:58:14,496
Come on. Look alive, big boy.

566
00:58:29,288 --> 00:58:30,380
Careful.

567
00:58:34,026 --> 00:58:34,856
Careful.

568
00:58:35,127 --> 00:58:35,855
Step up.

569
00:58:36,262 --> 00:58:37,126
Step up.

570
00:59:17,903 --> 00:59:19,165
Ain't this a party now?

571
00:59:19,672 --> 00:59:20,661
- Is it or what?
- Let him go.

572
00:59:20,973 --> 00:59:22,497
- Shoot him.
- See who you hit.

573
00:59:22,808 --> 00:59:24,207
Shoot the son of a bitch.

574
00:59:24,577 --> 00:59:25,305
Shoot him!

575
00:59:25,644 --> 00:59:28,169
Hit him, Percy!
Goddamn it! Hit him.

576
00:59:28,481 --> 00:59:29,846
Hit me, you limp noodle.

577
00:59:30,149 --> 00:59:30,945
Hit him, Percy!

578
00:59:31,250 --> 00:59:32,342
Goddamn it, hit him!

579
00:59:32,685 --> 00:59:33,811
Come on, Percy. Hit me.

580
00:59:34,753 --> 00:59:35,515
I'm warning you.

581
00:59:35,821 --> 00:59:37,152
You warning me?

582
00:59:37,756 --> 00:59:38,586
I'm warning you!

583
00:59:38,858 --> 00:59:40,792
- You're warning me?!
- Shoot him!

584
00:59:41,093 --> 00:59:42,390
Well, come on...

585
00:59:49,034 --> 00:59:49,966
You're a big fucker.

586
00:59:51,303 --> 00:59:52,668
Where'd you come from?

587
01:00:03,349 --> 01:00:05,715
Come on, Dean.
Come on, boy, get up.

588
01:00:06,018 --> 01:00:07,508
All right. Let it breathe.

589
01:00:08,187 --> 01:00:10,155
That's it. Just breathe.
Just breathe.

590
01:00:12,157 --> 01:00:13,784
Breathe. Breathe, boy.

591
01:00:14,126 --> 01:00:17,027
- Didn't see it coming.
- Come on, boy, breathe.

592
01:00:17,296 --> 01:00:19,230
Come on. Just breathe.

593
01:00:22,167 --> 01:00:24,192
We thought he was doped.

594
01:00:25,571 --> 01:00:28,734
Didn't we? Didn't we, all of us,
think he was doped?

595
01:00:29,041 --> 01:00:30,668
You didn't ask?

596
01:00:32,077 --> 01:00:33,874
I guess that's not a mistake...

597
01:00:34,313 --> 01:00:37,441
...you'll be needing to make again
anytime soon, is it?

598
01:00:51,597 --> 01:00:55,124
You go get Dean and Harry looked at.
Make sure they're all right.

599
01:00:55,668 --> 01:00:59,104
Percy, you make the report
to the warden for me.

600
01:00:59,405 --> 01:01:01,873
Say the situation's under control.
It's not a story.

601
01:01:02,174 --> 01:01:04,734
He won't appreciate you
drawing out the suspense.

602
01:01:05,044 --> 01:01:07,171
What about you?
You're about to collapse.

603
01:01:07,513 --> 01:01:10,778
I've got the Mile
till you all come back.

604
01:01:11,617 --> 01:01:13,551
Go on now. Go.

605
01:01:21,260 --> 01:01:24,286
Come on, boy.
Let's get you looked at.

606
01:01:49,989 --> 01:01:53,356
Boss, I needs to see you down here.

607
01:01:56,962 --> 01:02:00,090
This is not a good time, John Coffey...

608
01:02:00,399 --> 01:02:02,299
...not a good time at all.

609
01:02:02,568 --> 01:02:06,595
But I needs to see you, boss.
I needs to talk to you.

610
01:02:28,761 --> 01:02:29,989
Closer.

611
01:02:30,596 --> 01:02:32,564
You know you ain't
supposed to do that.

612
01:02:34,299 --> 01:02:36,199
Mind your business, Del.

613
01:02:45,911 --> 01:02:47,845
What do you want, John Coffey?

614
01:02:48,981 --> 01:02:49,970
Just to help it.

615
01:02:53,819 --> 01:02:55,150
Don't be afraid.

616
01:02:55,821 --> 01:02:56,719
Help!

617
01:02:57,623 --> 01:02:58,385
Help!

618
01:02:58,691 --> 01:03:00,318
Coffey's killing Boss Edgecomb!

619
01:03:00,626 --> 01:03:02,025
Help!

620
01:03:02,327 --> 01:03:03,316
What are you doing?

621
01:03:08,167 --> 01:03:09,930
Boss Howell! Help!

622
01:03:10,703 --> 01:03:12,330
Boss Stanton! Somebody, come!

623
01:03:31,156 --> 01:03:33,249
Help! Boss Howell! Boss Stanton!

624
01:03:33,592 --> 01:03:36,493
Somebody, come!
John Coffey's killing Boss Edgecomb!

625
01:03:36,762 --> 01:03:39,287
Del, for chrissakes, shut up!

626
01:04:25,978 --> 01:04:28,105
What did you just do to me?

627
01:04:30,149 --> 01:04:31,776
I helped it.

628
01:04:32,951 --> 01:04:34,441
Didn't I help it?

629
01:04:35,687 --> 01:04:37,780
I just took it back, is all.

630
01:04:38,724 --> 01:04:41,124
Awful tired now, boss.

631
01:04:41,727 --> 01:04:43,319
Dog-tired.

632
01:05:07,553 --> 01:05:10,488
Boss, what that man do to you?

633
01:06:13,051 --> 01:06:15,679
Hey, honey. How you feeling?

634
01:06:17,623 --> 01:06:20,285
Oh, not too bad.

635
01:06:21,627 --> 01:06:23,288
What did the doctor say?

636
01:06:25,631 --> 01:06:27,258
You know doctors.

637
01:06:27,799 --> 01:06:29,630
Gobbledygook, mostly.

638
01:06:30,802 --> 01:06:32,099
Gobbledygook.

639
01:06:47,419 --> 01:06:48,909
Having stew tonight.

640
01:06:59,331 --> 01:07:00,923
What are you doing?

641
01:07:07,739 --> 01:07:09,502
What does it feel like?

642
01:07:10,475 --> 01:07:12,841
Well, I know what it feels like.

643
01:07:16,548 --> 01:07:18,345
It feels great.

644
01:07:55,220 --> 01:07:57,814
Not that I'm complaining...

645
01:07:59,091 --> 01:08:02,720
...but we haven't gone four times
in one night since we were 19.

646
01:08:03,061 --> 01:08:05,325
Yeah, we did, at your mom's.

647
01:08:06,932 --> 01:08:08,832
Wanna tell me what's going on?

648
01:08:12,738 --> 01:08:13,670
Well...

649
01:08:15,407 --> 01:08:17,307
...see, the thing is...

650
01:08:18,610 --> 01:08:22,068
...I never actually made it in
to Dr. Bishop's yesterday.

651
01:08:25,317 --> 01:08:28,047
Brutal, Paul. Listen.

652
01:08:28,353 --> 01:08:32,722
I'm thinking of taking the morning
off sick. You cover the fort for me?

653
01:08:33,859 --> 01:08:36,020
That's swell. Thanks.

654
01:08:36,328 --> 01:08:38,853
Yeah, I'm sure I'll feel better.

655
01:08:47,205 --> 01:08:49,105
You're sure you ought to do this?

656
01:08:50,776 --> 01:08:52,903
I'm not sure what I'm sure of.

657
01:09:09,828 --> 01:09:12,729
Burt, you got some company.

658
01:09:13,498 --> 01:09:14,988
Can I offer you a cold drink?

659
01:09:15,333 --> 01:09:18,325
Yes, ma'am. A cold drink
would be fine. Thank you.

660
01:09:18,770 --> 01:09:21,762
Mr. Hammersmith, your office said
I might find you at home.

661
01:09:22,074 --> 01:09:23,632
Hope I'm not troubling you.

662
01:09:24,409 --> 01:09:26,400
Well, that depends, Mr?

663
01:09:26,711 --> 01:09:30,647
Paul Edgecomb. I'm E Block supervisor
up on Cold Mountain.

664
01:09:31,950 --> 01:09:33,247
The Green Mile.

665
01:09:33,518 --> 01:09:36,510
Yeah, I've heard of it.
Lost a few clients your way.

666
01:09:37,422 --> 01:09:39,014
I'd like to ask you about one.

667
01:09:41,293 --> 01:09:43,193
- Have a seat.
- Thank you.

668
01:09:48,033 --> 01:09:48,931
Which client?

669
01:09:51,269 --> 01:09:53,965
Now you got my curiosity aroused.

670
01:09:54,272 --> 01:09:55,500
John Coffey.

671
01:09:56,808 --> 01:09:57,832
Coffey.

672
01:09:58,410 --> 01:09:59,502
Causing you problems?

673
01:10:00,078 --> 01:10:03,514
Can't say he is. He doesn't like
the dark and cries on occasion...

674
01:10:03,849 --> 01:10:05,578
...but other than that...

675
01:10:05,884 --> 01:10:09,047
He cries, does he?
Got a lot to cry about, I'd say.

676
01:10:09,387 --> 01:10:10,820
You know what he did.

677
01:10:11,623 --> 01:10:13,557
I read the court transcript.

678
01:10:14,559 --> 01:10:15,287
Thank you, missus.

679
01:10:15,594 --> 01:10:17,221
My pleasure.

680
01:10:18,196 --> 01:10:18,924
IKids!

681
01:10:19,231 --> 01:10:21,392
Lunch is about ready.
Y'all come on up.

682
01:10:21,733 --> 01:10:22,927
Coming, Mama!

683
01:10:23,235 --> 01:10:26,261
What exactly are you
trying to find out?

684
01:10:26,972 --> 01:10:29,236
I wonder if he did anything
like that before.

685
01:10:30,775 --> 01:10:32,675
Why? Has he said anything?

686
01:10:32,944 --> 01:10:36,004
No, but a man who does
a thing like that...

687
01:10:36,314 --> 01:10:40,148
...has often developed a taste for it
over time. It occurred to me...

688
01:10:40,418 --> 01:10:44,252
...that it might be easy enough to
follow his back trail. Find out.

689
01:10:45,090 --> 01:10:48,787
A man his size, and colored to boot,
can't be that hard to trace.

690
01:10:49,094 --> 01:10:51,995
You'd think so, but you'd be wrong.

691
01:10:52,297 --> 01:10:54,322
Believe me, we tried.

692
01:10:55,267 --> 01:10:57,360
Like he'd dropped out of the sky.

693
01:10:58,270 --> 01:10:59,635
How can that be?

694
01:10:59,938 --> 01:11:04,034
We're in a depression.
A third of the country's out of work.

695
01:11:04,342 --> 01:11:08,278
People are drifting by the thousands,
looking for jobs, for greener grass.

696
01:11:08,613 --> 01:11:11,605
Even a giant like Coffey
wouldn't get noticed everywhere.

697
01:11:12,484 --> 01:11:14,714
Not until he kills
a couple of little girls.

698
01:11:15,687 --> 01:11:17,154
He is...

699
01:11:17,622 --> 01:11:19,556
...strange, I admit.

700
01:11:20,058 --> 01:11:24,256
But there doesn't seem to be
any real violence in him.

701
01:11:24,796 --> 01:11:27,162
I know violent men, Mr. Hammersmith.

702
01:11:27,465 --> 01:11:30,229
I deal with them day in and day out.

703
01:11:31,102 --> 01:11:33,662
You didn't come to ask me
whether he killed before.

704
01:11:33,972 --> 01:11:36,839
You came to see if I think
he did it at all.

705
01:11:38,310 --> 01:11:39,140
Do you?

706
01:11:41,213 --> 01:11:43,272
One seldom sees a less ambiguous case.

707
01:11:43,548 --> 01:11:45,516
He was found with the victims
in his arms.

708
01:11:45,817 --> 01:11:47,512
And yet you defended him.

709
01:11:48,653 --> 01:11:51,121
Everyone is entitled to a defense.

710
01:11:51,656 --> 01:11:53,146
IKids! Lunch!

711
01:11:53,491 --> 01:11:54,685
Y'all listen to your mama!

712
01:11:59,431 --> 01:12:00,898
I'll tell you something.

713
01:12:02,067 --> 01:12:05,559
You listen close too, because it
might be something you need to know.

714
01:12:05,870 --> 01:12:07,132
I'm listening.

715
01:12:08,673 --> 01:12:09,640
We had us a dog.

716
01:12:10,775 --> 01:12:12,709
Just a sweet mongrel.

717
01:12:13,011 --> 01:12:14,410
You know the kind.

718
01:12:15,880 --> 01:12:19,247
Well, in many ways,
a good mongrel dog is like a Negro.

719
01:12:20,218 --> 01:12:21,810
You get to know it.

720
01:12:22,153 --> 01:12:26,453
Often, you get to love it.
It is of no particular use...

721
01:12:26,725 --> 01:12:30,126
...but you keep it around
because you think it loves you.

722
01:12:31,763 --> 01:12:35,790
If you're lucky, Mr. Edgecomb, you
never have to find out any different.

723
01:12:36,968 --> 01:12:39,061
My wife and I were not so lucky.

724
01:12:41,139 --> 01:12:42,572
Caleb, come here for a second.

725
01:12:44,075 --> 01:12:45,167
Come here.

726
01:12:46,711 --> 01:12:47,871
Please, son.

727
01:12:49,547 --> 01:12:51,981
He still has the one good eye.

728
01:12:53,451 --> 01:12:55,544
I suppose he's lucky...

729
01:12:55,887 --> 01:12:58,185
...not to be completely blind.

730
01:13:00,959 --> 01:13:04,622
We get down on our knees and thank God
for that much at least.

731
01:13:05,397 --> 01:13:06,728
Right, Caleb?

732
01:13:09,634 --> 01:13:10,498
Go on in, now.

733
01:13:14,005 --> 01:13:16,872
That dog attacked my boy
for no reason.

734
01:13:17,542 --> 01:13:19,635
Just got it in his mind one day.

735
01:13:20,512 --> 01:13:21,911
The same with John Coffey.

736
01:13:22,180 --> 01:13:26,310
He was sorry afterwards.
Of that I have no doubt.

737
01:13:27,085 --> 01:13:28,814
But those little girls...

738
01:13:29,154 --> 01:13:31,520
...stayed raped and murdered.

739
01:13:32,257 --> 01:13:34,157
Maybe he'd never done it before.

740
01:13:36,027 --> 01:13:38,086
My dog never bit before.

741
01:13:39,931 --> 01:13:42,559
But I didn't concern myself with that.

742
01:13:43,668 --> 01:13:47,536
I went out with my rifle, grabbed
his collar and blew his brains out.

743
01:13:49,007 --> 01:13:50,065
Is Coffey guilty?

744
01:13:53,111 --> 01:13:54,738
Yes, he is.

745
01:13:55,447 --> 01:13:57,005
Don't you doubt it.

746
01:13:57,482 --> 01:13:59,848
And don't you turn your back on him.

747
01:14:00,785 --> 01:14:04,812
You may get away with it once
or even a hundred times...

748
01:14:05,790 --> 01:14:07,314
...but in the end...

749
01:14:09,461 --> 01:14:10,860
...you'll get bit.

750
01:14:23,508 --> 01:14:25,942
Oh, me! Oh, my!

751
01:14:32,851 --> 01:14:34,978
I'm smelling me some corn bread.

752
01:14:35,587 --> 01:14:37,384
It's from my missus.

753
01:14:41,159 --> 01:14:43,423
She wanted to thank you.

754
01:14:44,896 --> 01:14:46,227
Thank me for what?

755
01:14:46,731 --> 01:14:47,891
Well, you know.

756
01:14:50,735 --> 01:14:52,066
For helping me.

757
01:14:52,837 --> 01:14:54,304
Helping you with what?

758
01:14:55,106 --> 01:14:56,130
You know.

759
01:15:02,747 --> 01:15:04,647
Was your missus pleased?

760
01:15:06,584 --> 01:15:08,108
Several times.

761
01:15:23,768 --> 01:15:27,169
John, I can smell that from over here.
I surely can.

762
01:15:30,141 --> 01:15:32,336
Can I give Del and Mr. Jingles some?

763
01:15:33,044 --> 01:15:36,502
Well, it's yours, John.
You can do with it as you please.

764
01:15:39,684 --> 01:15:43,051
Here. This for Del and Mr. Jingles.

765
01:15:43,888 --> 01:15:47,415
Hey! What about me?
I'm gonna get some too, ain't I?

766
01:15:49,661 --> 01:15:52,687
It's yours, John. As you please.

767
01:15:53,398 --> 01:15:55,958
I think I'll just keep the rest, then.

768
01:16:01,906 --> 01:16:04,033
Courtesy of the gentleman
across the way.

769
01:16:06,377 --> 01:16:09,073
John, that's so very fine of you.

770
01:16:10,148 --> 01:16:13,811
I thank you. Mr. Jingle thank you.
My mama'd thank you too, but she dead.

771
01:16:14,719 --> 01:16:15,879
Welcome.

772
01:16:17,322 --> 01:16:21,315
What about me? Don't you
hold out on me, you big dummy nigger.

773
01:16:25,530 --> 01:16:26,929
Here come the boss man.

774
01:16:27,866 --> 01:16:30,266
You'll keep a civil tongue
on my block.

775
01:16:41,746 --> 01:16:43,680
You get that one for free.

776
01:16:44,749 --> 01:16:46,307
But that's the last one.

777
01:16:47,185 --> 01:16:50,052
That's it?
Just that little itty-bitty one?

778
01:16:50,722 --> 01:16:53,919
I guess I'm gonna have to
pay you out for the rest.

779
01:17:08,373 --> 01:17:09,271
Good shot, weren't it?

780
01:17:11,643 --> 01:17:13,668
The look on your face!

781
