a few questions.

1546
02:34:50,141 --> 02:34:53,338
One minute, he was fine,
and the next, blammo!

1547
02:34:53,644 --> 02:34:55,976
Dirty bastard grabbed him
through the bars.

1548
02:34:56,247 --> 02:34:58,408
Scared the boy so bad, he wet hisself.

1549
02:34:59,850 --> 02:35:02,683
See, we didn't even see it happen.

1550
02:35:06,657 --> 02:35:09,922
I'll cover for you as much as I can...

1551
02:35:10,194 --> 02:35:12,424
...even if it means my job.

1552
02:35:13,164 --> 02:35:14,927
But I have to know...

1553
02:35:15,399 --> 02:35:18,527
...does this have anything to do
with what happened at my house?

1554
02:35:21,505 --> 02:35:22,972
Does it, Paul?

1555
02:35:24,942 --> 02:35:26,136
No.

1556
02:36:53,631 --> 02:36:57,362
Does Hal know?
That Coffey's innocent, I mean.

1557
02:36:58,702 --> 02:37:00,363
Well, can he help?

1558
02:37:01,005 --> 02:37:03,735
Does he have the influence to do
something about this?

1559
02:37:04,008 --> 02:37:05,475
Stop the execution?

1560
02:37:05,776 --> 02:37:06,708
No.

1561
02:37:09,947 --> 02:37:11,380
Then don't tell him.

1562
02:37:12,116 --> 02:37:14,277
If it can't help, don't tell him.

1563
02:37:14,752 --> 02:37:15,912
Ever.

1564
02:37:18,322 --> 02:37:19,721
I won't.

1565
02:37:31,502 --> 02:37:33,800
There's no way out of this for you,
is there?

1566
02:37:35,339 --> 02:37:36,636
No.

1567
02:37:37,741 --> 02:37:40,232
And I've been thinking about it,
believe me.

1568
02:37:40,511 --> 02:37:43,776
I've been running it through my head
any number of ways.

1569
02:37:46,250 --> 02:37:48,275
I'll tell you the truth, honey.

1570
02:37:49,954 --> 02:37:54,687
I've done some things in my life
that I am not proud of...

1571
02:37:55,326 --> 02:38:00,127
...but this is the first time I've
ever felt real danger of hell.

1572
02:38:01,198 --> 02:38:02,495
Hell?

1573
02:38:08,439 --> 02:38:09,997
Talk to him.

1574
02:38:11,242 --> 02:38:13,005
Talk to John.

1575
02:38:14,845 --> 02:38:16,813
Find out what he wants.

1576
02:38:33,797 --> 02:38:34,957
Hello, boss.

1577
02:38:36,033 --> 02:38:37,295
Hello, John.

1578
02:38:38,802 --> 02:38:41,134
I guess you know we're
coming down to it now.

1579
02:38:41,972 --> 02:38:43,633
Another couple of days.

1580
02:38:57,254 --> 02:38:59,984
Is there anything special
you wanna eat that night?

1581
02:39:00,457 --> 02:39:02,687
We can rustle you up most anything.

1582
02:39:13,070 --> 02:39:17,666
Meat loaf be nice.
Mashed taters, gravy.

1583
02:39:18,008 --> 02:39:19,339
Okra.

1584
02:39:20,511 --> 02:39:23,241
Maybe some of that fine corn bread
your missus make...

1585
02:39:24,181 --> 02:39:26,149
...if she don't mind.

1586
02:39:28,552 --> 02:39:29,883
Now...

1587
02:39:30,487 --> 02:39:35,322
...what about a preacher?
Somebody to say a little prayer with.

1588
02:39:35,592 --> 02:39:37,685
Don't want no preacher.

1589
02:39:38,796 --> 02:39:41,264
You can say a prayer, if you like.

1590
02:39:41,966 --> 02:39:43,024
Me?

1591
02:39:46,103 --> 02:39:48,867
Suppose I could, if it came to that.

1592
02:39:57,147 --> 02:39:59,877
I have to ask you something
very important now.

1593
02:40:01,618 --> 02:40:03,711
I know what you gonna say.

1594
02:40:04,288 --> 02:40:05,721
You don't have to say it.

1595
02:40:06,123 --> 02:40:09,388
No, I do. I do.
I have to say it.

1596
02:40:13,397 --> 02:40:15,661
Tell me what you want me to do.

1597
02:40:16,633 --> 02:40:18,567
You want me to take you out of here?

1598
02:40:19,870 --> 02:40:23,806
Just let you run away?
See how far you could get?

1599
02:40:25,342 --> 02:40:27,970
Why would you do such a foolish thing?

1600
02:40:30,047 --> 02:40:32,106
On the day of my judgment...

1601
02:40:33,017 --> 02:40:35,110
...when I stand before God...

1602
02:40:35,386 --> 02:40:39,152
...and He asks me why did I...

1603
02:40:39,423 --> 02:40:41,983
...did I kill one of His true...

1604
02:40:42,926 --> 02:40:44,416
...miracles...

1605
02:40:45,662 --> 02:40:47,755
...what am I going to say?

1606
02:40:48,766 --> 02:40:50,427
That it was my job?

1607
02:40:52,669 --> 02:40:54,603
It's my job.

1608
02:40:54,972 --> 02:40:59,534
You tell God the Father
it was a kindness you done.

1609
02:41:02,746 --> 02:41:05,237
I know you're hurting and worrying.

1610
02:41:06,050 --> 02:41:09,577
I can feel it on you.
But you ought to quit on it now.

1611
02:41:10,854 --> 02:41:13,789
I want it to be over and done with.

1612
02:41:14,525 --> 02:41:15,958
I do.

1613
02:41:20,464 --> 02:41:22,398
I'm tired, boss.

1614
02:41:23,867 --> 02:41:28,167
Tired of being on the road,
lonely as a sparrow in the rain.

1615
02:41:29,440 --> 02:41:32,136
I'm tired of never having me
a buddy to be with...

1616
02:41:32,776 --> 02:41:37,270
...to tell me where we's going to,
coming from, or why.

1617
02:41:38,215 --> 02:41:42,345
Mostly, I'm tired of people
being ugly to each other.

1618
02:41:43,554 --> 02:41:47,456
I'm tired of all the pain
I feel and hear in the world...

1619
02:41:47,724 --> 02:41:49,316
...every day.

1620
02:41:49,760 --> 02:41:51,660
There's too much of it.

1621
02:41:52,062 --> 02:41:55,828
It's like pieces of glass
in my head...

1622
02:41:56,100 --> 02:41:58,330
...all the time.

1623
02:41:59,903 --> 02:42:01,894
Can you understand?

1624
02:42:04,908 --> 02:42:07,809
Yes, John, I think I can.

1625
02:42:10,247 --> 02:42:13,546
Well, there must be something
we can do for you, John.

1626
02:42:15,819 --> 02:42:17,753
There must be something that you want.

1627
02:42:27,264 --> 02:42:31,701
I ain't never seen me a flicker show.

1628
02:42:32,269 --> 02:42:34,328
Heaven

1629
02:42:34,605 --> 02:42:36,698
I'm in heaven

1630
02:42:37,674 --> 02:42:42,441
And my heart beats so
That I can hardly speak

1631
02:42:44,348 --> 02:42:49,115
And I seem to find
The happiness I seek

1632
02:42:50,787 --> 02:42:55,554
When we're out together
Dancing cheek to cheek

1633
02:43:57,688 --> 02:44:00,054
Why, they's angels.

1634
02:44:01,024 --> 02:44:03,618
Angels, just like up in heaven.

1635
02:45:04,354 --> 02:45:06,288
I'll be all right, fellas.

1636
02:45:07,758 --> 02:45:09,953
This here's the hard part.

1637
02:45:11,328 --> 02:45:12,795
I'll be all right in a while.

1638
02:45:15,666 --> 02:45:18,464
I should have this just for now.

1639
02:45:22,539 --> 02:45:24,905
I'll give it back after.

1640
02:45:28,045 --> 02:45:32,539
You know, I fell asleep this afternoon
and had me a dream.

1641
02:45:33,850 --> 02:45:35,841
I dreamed about Del's mouse.

1642
02:45:37,120 --> 02:45:38,246
Did you, John?

1643
02:45:39,122 --> 02:45:43,456
I dreamed Mr. Jingles got down to
that place Boss Howell talked about.

1644
02:45:43,727 --> 02:45:45,957
That Mouseville place.

1645
02:45:46,296 --> 02:45:48,560
I dreamed there's kids.

1646
02:45:49,199 --> 02:45:52,566
And how they laughed
at his tricks. My!

1647
02:45:55,138 --> 02:45:58,869
I dreamed that those two little
blonde-headed girls was there.

1648
02:45:59,142 --> 02:46:00,939
They's laughing too.

1649
02:46:01,211 --> 02:46:04,078
I put my arms around them
and set them on my knees.

1650
02:46:04,348 --> 02:46:08,341
And they was no blood coming out
of they hair, and they's just fine.

1651
02:46:08,652 --> 02:46:11,917
We all watched Mr. Jingles
roll that spool.

1652
02:46:13,490 --> 02:46:16,857
How we did laugh.
Fit to bust, we was!

1653
02:46:35,178 --> 02:46:39,171
They's lots of folks here
that hate me. Lots!

1654
02:46:41,184 --> 02:46:43,152
I can feel it.

1655
02:46:43,487 --> 02:46:45,079
It's like bees stinging me.

1656
02:46:45,522 --> 02:46:47,820
Well, feel how we feel, then.

1657
02:46:49,192 --> 02:46:50,284
We don't hate you.

1658
02:46:51,795 --> 02:46:53,285
Can you feel that?

1659
02:46:55,599 --> 02:46:57,692
IKill him twice, you boys!

1660
02:46:58,535 --> 02:47:02,471
You go on and kill that raping
babykiller twice!

1661
02:47:02,739 --> 02:47:04,502
That'd be fine!

1662
02:47:21,258 --> 02:47:23,658
Wipe your face before
you stand up, Dean.

1663
02:47:23,927 --> 02:47:25,155
Yes, sir.

1664
02:47:37,507 --> 02:47:38,496
Roll on one.

1665
02:47:46,583 --> 02:47:50,019
Does it hurt yet? I hope it does.

1666
02:47:50,921 --> 02:47:53,116
I hope it hurts like hell.

1667
02:47:55,158 --> 02:47:57,626
John Coffey, you've been condemned
to die in the electric chair...

1668
02:47:57,928 --> 02:47:59,122
...by a jury of your peers.

1669
02:47:59,429 --> 02:48:02,762
Sentence imposed by a judge
in good standing in this state.

1670
02:48:03,300 --> 02:48:06,463
Do you have anything to say
before sentence is carried out?

1671
02:48:08,271 --> 02:48:10,739
I'm sorry for what I am.

1672
02:48:22,819 --> 02:48:24,446
Please, boss...

1673
02:48:25,956 --> 02:48:28,584
...don't put that thing over my face.

1674
02:48:29,860 --> 02:48:32,124
Don't put me in the dark.

1675
02:48:32,963 --> 02:48:35,227
I's afraid of the dark.

1676
02:48:44,975 --> 02:48:46,567
All right, John.

1677
02:49:06,830 --> 02:49:09,799
Heaven, I'm in heaven

1678
02:49:10,066 --> 02:49:12,830
Heaven, heaven

1679
02:49:13,103 --> 02:49:14,866
I'm in heaven

1680
02:49:15,505 --> 02:49:18,030
Heaven, heaven

1681
02:49:18,341 --> 02:49:19,968
I'm in heaven

1682
02:49:40,964 --> 02:49:42,488
John Coffey...

1683
02:49:43,600 --> 02:49:46,660
...electricity shall pass through
your body until you are dead...

1684
02:49:46,937 --> 02:49:49,030
...in accordance with state law.

1685
02:49:51,474 --> 02:49:55,137
May God have mercy on your soul.

1686
02:50:33,917 --> 02:50:35,817
You have to say it.

1687
02:50:37,520 --> 02:50:39,750
You have to give the order.

1688
02:50:57,841 --> 02:51:00,071
He killed them with they love.

1689
02:51:00,343 --> 02:51:05,076
That's how it is every day
all over the world.

1690
02:51:18,962 --> 02:51:20,327
Roll on two.

1691
02:53:05,068 --> 02:53:08,367
It was the last execution
I ever took part in.

1692
02:53:08,738 --> 02:53:12,401
I just couldn't do it anymore
after that. Brutal either.

1693
02:53:13,643 --> 02:53:18,239
We both transferred out,
took jobs with Boys' Correctional.

1694
02:53:18,581 --> 02:53:20,242
It was all right.

1695
02:53:21,017 --> 02:53:23,884
"Catch them young" became my motto.

1696
02:53:27,157 --> 02:53:28,181
You don't believe me.

1697
02:53:29,159 --> 02:53:31,593
I don't imagine you'd lie to me, Paul.

1698
02:53:32,495 --> 02:53:34,588
- It's just that...
- It's quite a story.

1699
02:53:34,864 --> 02:53:37,025
It's quite a story.

1700
02:53:37,500 --> 02:53:39,798
One thing I don't understand.

1701
02:53:40,103 --> 02:53:41,798
You said you and Jan...

1702
02:53:42,105 --> 02:53:45,597
...had a grown son in 1935.

1703
02:53:45,942 --> 02:53:47,375
Is that right?

1704
02:53:47,811 --> 02:53:49,711
The math doesn't work, does it?

1705
02:53:55,451 --> 02:53:57,976
Do you feel up to taking a walk?

1706
02:54:18,708 --> 02:54:20,073
Watch your step.

1707
02:54:20,643 --> 02:54:22,907
Now let your eyes adjust.

1708
02:54:34,824 --> 02:54:35,756
There.

1709
02:54:39,662 --> 02:54:41,323
Wake up, old fella.

1710
02:54:41,664 --> 02:54:42,858
Wake up.

1711
02:54:46,502 --> 02:54:50,302
Paul, it isn't. It can't be.

1712
02:54:54,577 --> 02:54:55,839
Come over here, boy.

1713
02:54:56,412 --> 02:54:58,710
Come on over here and see this lady.

1714
02:55:01,684 --> 02:55:04,619
That can't be Mr. Jingles.

1715
02:55:27,377 --> 02:55:29,902
Go on, you can do it.

1716
02:55:37,086 --> 02:55:41,455
This isn't exactly the Mouseville
we had in mind, is it?

1717
02:55:42,325 --> 02:55:46,227
But we make do. Don't we, old fella?

1718
02:55:52,735 --> 02:55:56,330
I think Mr. Jingles
happened by accident.

1719
02:55:56,839 --> 02:56:01,640
I think when we electrocuted Del,
and it all went so badly...

1720
02:56:01,911 --> 02:56:04,209
...well, John could feel that,
you know.

1721
02:56:04,514 --> 02:56:07,847
And I think a part of...

1722
02:56:08,184 --> 02:56:10,709
...whatever magic was inside of him...

1723
02:56:11,120 --> 02:56:14,351
...just leapt into my tiny friend here.

1724
02:56:15,591 --> 02:56:17,525
As for me...

1725
02:56:18,761 --> 02:56:21,252
...John had to give me
a part of himself...

1726
02:56:21,597 --> 02:56:23,690
...a gift, the way he saw it...

1727
02:56:24,100 --> 02:56:27,467
...so that I could see for myself
what Wild Bill had done.

1728
02:56:29,939 --> 02:56:32,100
When John did that...

1729
02:56:33,609 --> 02:56:35,873
...when he took my hand...

1730
02:56:36,946 --> 02:56:40,780
...a part of the power
that worked through him...

1731
02:56:41,784 --> 02:56:43,547
...spilled into me.

1732
02:56:44,020 --> 02:56:45,783
He... what?

1733
02:56:46,289 --> 02:56:49,725
He infected you with life?

1734
02:56:51,394 --> 02:56:53,658
It's as good a word as any.

1735
02:56:55,231 --> 02:56:58,064
He infected us both,
didn't he, Mr. Jingles?

1736
02:56:58,334 --> 02:56:59,733
With life.

1737
02:57:03,873 --> 02:57:06,899
I'm 108 years old, Elaine.

1738
02:57:07,210 --> 02:57:11,476
I was 44 the year that John Coffey
walked the Green Mile.

1739
02:57:14,484 --> 02:57:18,147
You mustn't blame John.
He couldn't help what happened.

1740
02:57:18,488 --> 02:57:22,948
He was just a force of nature.

1741
02:57:23,493 --> 02:57:27,623
I've lived to see
some amazing things, Ellie.

1742
02:57:28,731 --> 02:57:31,632
Another century come to pass.

1743
02:57:34,437 --> 02:57:38,840
But I've had to see my friends and
loved ones die off through the years.

1744
02:57:39,275 --> 02:57:41,266
Hal and Melinda...

1745
02:57:41,778 --> 02:57:43,143
...Brutus Howell...

1746
02:57:43,379 --> 02:57:46,007
...my wife, my boy.

1747
02:57:49,052 --> 02:57:50,815
And you, Elaine.

1748
02:57:51,888 --> 02:57:53,617
You'll die too.

1749
02:57:55,191 --> 02:57:59,525
And my curse is knowing
that I'll be there to see it.

1750
02:58:01,030 --> 02:58:03,396
It's my atonement, you see.

1751
02:58:04,033 --> 02:58:05,694
It's my punishment...

1752
02:58:05,968 --> 02:58:08,528
...for letting John Coffey
ride the lightning.

1753
02:58:10,306 --> 02:58:13,002
For killing a miracle of God.

1754
02:58:14,610 --> 02:58:17,272
Almighty, everlasting God...

1755
02:58:17,680 --> 02:58:20,012
...the source of all being and life.

1756
02:58:20,316 --> 02:58:24,514
You'll be gone like all the others.
I'll have to stay.

1757
02:58:26,622 --> 02:58:30,752
I'll die eventually.
Of that I'm sure.

1758
02:58:31,561 --> 02:58:35,497
I have no illusions of immortality.

1759
02:58:35,932 --> 02:58:38,366
But I will have wished for death...

1760
02:58:39,135 --> 02:58:41,262
...long before death finds me.

1761
02:58:42,438 --> 02:58:46,204
In truth, I wish for it already.

1762
02:58:58,354 --> 02:59:00,288
Mr. Jingles?

1763
02:59:09,332 --> 02:59:11,425
Where you been?

1764
02:59:11,934 --> 02:59:15,131
Been worried about you, boy.
You hungry?

1765
02:59:16,038 --> 02:59:18,404
Let's see if we can find you
something to eat.

1766
02:59:19,609 --> 02:59:23,272
A few crumbs anyway.
I know you'd like that.

1767
02:59:24,780 --> 02:59:26,042
Look at you.

1768
02:59:27,817 --> 02:59:31,651
I lie in bed most nights
thinking about it.

1769
02:59:31,921 --> 02:59:33,855
And I wait.

1770
02:59:34,857 --> 02:59:37,519
I think about all the people
I've loved...

1771
02:59:37,793 --> 02:59:39,886
...now long gone.

1772
02:59:40,696 --> 02:59:43,062
I think about my beautiful Jan...

1773
02:59:43,332 --> 02:59:46,301
...how I lost her so many years ago.

1774
02:59:47,737 --> 02:59:52,299
And I think about all of us walking
our own Green Mile...

1775
02:59:52,575 --> 02:59:55,169
...each in our own time.

1776
02:59:56,312 --> 02:59:59,406
But one thought
more than any other...

1777
02:59:59,682 --> 03:00:02,276
...keeps me awake most nights:

1778
03:00:03,519 --> 03:00:07,421
If he could make a mouse
live so long...

1779
03:00:07,990 --> 03:00:10,982
...how much longer do I have?

1780
03:00:14,363 --> 03:00:17,059
We each owe a death.

1781
03:00:17,333 --> 03:00:19,767
There are no exceptions.

1782
03:00:20,603 --> 03:00:22,537
But, oh, God...

1783
03:00:23,506 --> 03:00:25,235
...sometimes...

1784
03:00:25,908 --> 03:00:29,400
...the Green Mile seems so long.

